IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: School to career education for Maine's at-risk students.
IRS990.MissionDesc: To identify students who face barriers to education, and to guide each one on to a successful path toward continued education, a meaningful career, and productive adulthood.
IRS990.Desc: School-to-work transition and opportunity awareness program provides essential services to at risk Maine students to remain in school, enhance academic performance, graduate, and become gainfully employed.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The IDA Opportunity Passport Program is a financial literacy and matched savings program that helps youth develop a general understanding about personal finances and goal setting. Youth benefit from matching funds for purchases from the approved categories of housing, education, vehicles, investments, medical expenses, and other categories approved on a case-by-case basis.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A small portion of staff member time is spent advocating for legislation and general support of disadvantaged students to ensure that they have access to quality educational and workforce training opportunities.

OtherLiabilitiesOrgGrp.Desc: Due to related party - Generation US

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The endowment fund has been established to support the Organization's mission and further diversify its revenue base over time.
Management of the Organization believes it has no material uncertain tax positions and accordingly, will not recognize any liability for unrecognized tax benefits.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: Grants given to qualified enrollees for approved purchases such as housing, education, and medical.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The form 990 is prepared by the Organization's independent accountants. Prior to filing, the Organization's Finance Committee reviews and recommends acceptance to the Executive Committee. The Executive Committee then reviews and votes to accept and sends out to the entire governing body.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Current board members and key employees are required to complete a conflict of interest statement annually. New board members complete the statement upon joining the board. Any conflicts brought to the attention of management or the board are addressed and resolved timely.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The organization has an evaluation process in place. All key employees have an annual evaluation. The President's compensation is decided on by the Board of Directors after his review. They also have an independent salary study done using Maine Association for Non Profits, Guide Star Survey of Non Profit Executives and Non Profit Times Salary Survey. Those surveys were used for determining compensation for the President and top management.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: All documents are made available upon request.
The Organization's Finance committee has responsibility for oversight of the audit and selection of the independent accountant. The process is unchanged from the previous year.
